//
the full-time indie dream is, for all intents and purposes, dead.

the supply of game developers and games is steadily increasing to
the point that most additional games added to the app stores don't
matter.

indie developers, billion dollar companies and weekend warriors.

the market is now structured for the full-time indie to fail.

one obvious defensive move would be to see indies teaming up
in larger studios to provide more of a safety net.

that if you're going mobile, you need to be able to make a lot of
games in a short period.